issue.description:
Clause 5.3
Summary/Abstract/Keywords: Inconsistent semantics due to non-unique name
Problem Description: Instances of ascribable_state, ascribable_state_relationship, state_observed, state_observed_relationship and state_observed_role entities should have a unique name within a dataset. Otherwise two or more instances with the same name but different description/definition could possibly exist, which would lead to inconsistent or ambiguous semantics. Modify the ENTITY definitions with a UNIQUE constraint as follows: UNIQUE ur1: name;
